genresAdvancedInfo.name: punta
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Punta is a traditional Garifuna music style from Central America. It features a call-and-response style of singing, accompanied by drums and percussion instruments. The music is characterized by its upbeat tempo, syncopated rhythms, and lively dance moves. The lyrics often celebrate Garifuna culture and history, as well as everyday life and love. Punta has become popular throughout the Caribbean and beyond, and is often performed at festivals and other cultural events.
